Sales Performance Dashboard – Power BI  (Data is imported From Chandoo.org)

•	This project demonstrates a Sales Performance Dashboard built using Power BI.
•	Data was connected and cleaned using Power Query.
•	Monthly target data was reshaped using the unpivot feature.
•	Multiple tables such as Actuals, Targets, Calendar, and People were used.
•	Relationships were created to form a proper data model.
•	The data model supports filtering by date, team, and salesperson.
•	DAX was used to calculate total sales and target values.
•	Variance and variance percentage measures were created using DAX.
•	Year-to-date (YTD) calculations were implemented using time intelligence.
•	The FILTER and CALCULATE functions were used in DAX measures.
•	Emoji indicators were added using DAX for better visual understanding.
•	KPI cards were created using the new Power BI card visual.
•	Bar charts were used to compare actual sales against targets.
•	Tables include sparklines to show sales trends.
•	Custom data labels were applied to improve readability.
•	Report themes were used for a consistent look and feel.
•	Tables were formatted for executive-level reporting.
•	Slicers were added for interactive filtering.
•	The Smart Narrative feature was used to explain insights automatically.
•	The final dashboard provides clear and easy-to-understand sales insights.
